headline: Accenture to acquire Cabel Industry, terms not disclosed
summary: Accenture (ACN) has entered into an agreement with the Fibonacci Group to acquire Cabel Industry, an Italian technology company that provides specialized core banking and IT managed services to mid-size financial institutions. Terms of the transaction were not disclosed. Completion of the acquisition is subject to customary closing conditions. headline: 5 Revealing Analyst Questions From Accenture’s Q4 Earnings Call
summary: Accenture’s fourth quarter results came in ahead of Wall Street’s expectations, with management highlighting broad-based demand for complex digital transformation and the scaling of enterprise artificial intelligence (AI) projects as key contributors. CEO Julie Sweet noted that the company’s client base is increasingly seeking end-to-end reinvention rather than isolated AI pilots, with over $1.1 billion in advanced AI revenue and a near doubling of AI-related bookings year-over-year.
